If you are not willing to check on this game at least once a cycle, please do not sign up. Thank you!

Hello @Snackxile
5
3
3
1
19:52
I think it is time you find out what you signed up for.
19:52
.
19:52
.
19:52
.
19:52
Since the players get to experience the many joys of The Tank, we wanted to do something for yall to have some fun with it as well!
19:53
Welcome to Snackxile, a spectator game where you must avoid and survive exile!
6
2
19:53
19:53
For those familiar with Rock ORGs, this will work similar to those with a slight twist
4
19:53
If you are not familiar, it is essentially a mini-ORG but without all the bells and whistles.
19:53
Each cycle, you will be assigned a random player in the game. For that cycle you are tied to that player. If their tribe wins immunity, so do you (same for individual immunity when we get there).
19:53
If your player is on a tribe attending tribal council, you go to your own tribal council with the other Snackxile players on your tribe! There you will go through the normal voting process, voting another member of your Snackxile tribe out of the game.
19:53
19:53
Here is where the twist comes in
19:53
.
19:53
.
19:53
.
19:54
When someone is voted out, they are not immediately out of the game.
6
3
19:54
Instead, they get sent to Snackxile Island.
19:54
There, they will be given a random task to complete by the end of the current challenge cycle.
1
1
3
19:54
If they fail to do so, they are eliminated from the game.
19:54
However, if they succeed.
19:54
.
19:54
.
19:54
.
19:54
They get to choose who is eliminated that round! (Out of the members of their tribe for that round)
3
3
2
19:54
19:54
This will last the entire season. And similar to the actual game, eventually a jury will form and they will vote for the ultimate winner at the end of the season.
19:55
The only place you may talk about snackxile in the server is in this chat. Only those playing Snackxile can speak in here. You may create public or private threads as you please.
19:55
As always, please ask if you have any questions. Hopefully as the game progresses how this works becomes more clear.
